## 1. Purpose and Scope

### 1.1 Purpose

This Security Program establishes the policies, procedures, and controls necessary to protect the assets, employees, customers, and operations of the auto repair business. The program addresses physical, operational, informational, and cybersecurity risks specific to an automotive service environment.

### 1.2 Scope

This program applies to:
- All employees, including full-time, part-time, and seasonal staff
- Contractors, vendors, and third parties with access to the premises
- All physical locations, including the shop floor, office, parking lot, and storage areas
- All systems, equipment, and data used in business operations

### 1.3 Goals

- Prevent theft of vehicles, parts, tools, cash, and customer property
- Protect customer personal and financial data
- Ensure employee safety and reduce workplace security incidents
- Maintain compliance with applicable laws and regulations
- Enable quick, effective response to security incidents

