## 6. Employee Security

### 6.1 Hiring Practices

- Conduct a background check on all new hires prior to employment, including:
  - Criminal history check
  - Driving record check (required for roles involving vehicle operation)
  - Employment history verification
- Obtain written authorization from candidates before conducting checks.

### 6.2 Onboarding

- All new employees must review and sign acknowledgment of this Security Program before beginning work.
- Employees must be briefed on key security procedures relevant to their role: key handling, customer vehicle intake, cash handling, and data privacy.

### 6.3 Termination Procedures

Upon termination of employment (voluntary or involuntary):

- [ ] Collect all keys, key fobs, and access cards immediately
- [ ] Revoke alarm system codes
- [ ] Disable or remove computer/system access accounts
- [ ] Recover any company-owned devices (phones, tablets, laptops)
- [ ] Change relevant safe combinations and cabinet lock codes if the employee had access
- [ ] Document the above steps in the employee's file

### 6.4 Employee Conduct

- Employees must not share alarm codes, key cabinet combinations, or computer passwords with others.
- Employees must not allow unauthorized individuals into restricted areas.
- Employees must not conduct personal transactions using customer vehicle information or data.
- Theft of any company, customer, or co-worker property is grounds for immediate termination and may result in criminal prosecution.

### 6.5 Reporting Security Concerns

Employees are expected and encouraged to report:
- Suspicious persons or vehicles on or near the property
- Missing or misplaced keys, tools, or parts
- Suspected theft or unauthorized access
- Any security system malfunctions

Reports should be made to the shop manager or owner without fear of retaliation.

