## 7. Cybersecurity

### 7.1 Network Security

- The shop's Wi-Fi network must use WPA3 (or WPA2 minimum) encryption with a strong password.
- A **separate guest Wi-Fi network** must be provided for customer use; customers must not have access to the business network.
- The router/firewall must use the manufacturer's latest firmware and must not use default login credentials.
- Business systems (POS, shop management software, computers) must be on a dedicated, private network segment.

### 7.2 Password Policy

- All accounts on business systems must use passwords that are:
  - At least 12 characters long
  - A mix of uppercase, lowercase, numbers, and symbols
  - Unique per account (no password reuse across systems)
- Passwords must never be written on sticky notes or left in visible areas.
- A password manager is recommended for managing credentials securely.
- Default passwords on all routers, cameras, and systems must be changed before deployment.

### 7.3 Software and Updates

- All computers and devices must run supported operating systems with automatic security updates enabled.
- Shop management software and POS systems must be kept current with vendor-provided updates.
- Antivirus/anti-malware software must be installed and updated on all Windows computers.

### 7.4 Email and Phishing

- Employees must not click links or open attachments in unexpected or suspicious emails.
- Payment-related requests received via email (e.g., changes to vendor bank accounts) must be verified by phone before acting on them.
- The business email account must use multi-factor authentication (MFA) if the provider supports it.

### 7.5 Data Backup

- Customer and business data must be backed up at least weekly.
- Backups must be stored offsite or in a secure cloud service — not only on the same local machine.
- Backup restoration must be tested at least once per year.

### 7.6 Device Security

- Computers must have screen lock enabled and activate after no more than 10 minutes of inactivity.
- Employees must lock workstations when stepping away.
- No personal USB drives or external storage may be connected to business computers without manager approval.

