## 9. Environmental and Safety Security

### 9.1 Hazardous Materials

- Flammable materials (oil, solvents, fuels) must be stored in approved, labeled containers in a dedicated storage area away from ignition sources.
- Safety Data Sheets (SDS) must be readily accessible for all chemicals used.
- Waste oil and chemicals must be disposed of through a licensed waste hauler — never poured down drains.

### 9.2 Fire Prevention

- Fire extinguishers must be mounted in visible, accessible locations throughout the shop and inspected annually.
- The shop must not accumulate combustible waste (rags, cardboard, etc.) near heat sources or ignition points.
- Emergency exit routes must be clearly marked and kept unobstructed at all times.
- A fire evacuation plan must be posted and communicated to all employees.

### 9.3 Tool and Equipment Security

- High-value tools and equipment (diagnostic scanners, lifts, specialty tools) must be inventoried annually.
- Tools left unattended overnight must be secured in locked toolboxes or storage rooms.
- Serial numbers for high-value tools and equipment should be recorded and stored in a secure document.

