## 10. Vendor and Supplier Security

- Vendors and service providers who access the premises (e.g., parts delivery, equipment repair) must check in with a designated employee and must not be left unescorted in restricted areas.
- Before sharing any business or customer data with a third-party software provider, review their privacy policy and data security practices.
- Vendor relationships involving payment processing or customer data handling must use a signed agreement that includes data security and confidentiality obligations.
- Terminate vendor access (physical and digital) promptly when a vendor relationship ends.

---

## 11. Compliance and Legal

### 11.1 Privacy Laws

- Comply with applicable state and federal consumer privacy laws regarding the collection, use, and protection of customer personal information.
- Do not sell or share customer data with third parties for marketing purposes without explicit consent.

### 11.2 Payment Card Industry (PCI DSS)

- Any business accepting credit or debit cards must comply with PCI DSS requirements applicable to its processing method. Consult your payment processor for guidance on your required compliance level.

### 11.3 Employment Law

- Background check procedures must comply with the Fair Credit Reporting Act (FCRA) and applicable state laws.

### 11.4 Insurance

- Maintain adequate business insurance coverage including:
  - General liability
  - Garage keepers liability (covers customer vehicles in your care)
  - Commercial property (covers tools, equipment, inventory)
  - Cyber liability insurance (recommended)
- Review coverage annually with your insurance agent.

