## 12. Security Roles and Responsibilities

| Role | Responsibilities |
|---|---|
| **Owner** | Overall accountability for the security program; approve policies; manage safe and alarm master codes; review incident logs |
| **Shop Manager** | Day-to-day enforcement of security procedures; manage key cabinet; conduct opening/closing security checks; onboard employees on security policies |
| **Service Writer** | Customer vehicle intake documentation; key cabinet management; verify customer identity at vehicle release; secure customer data |
| **Technician** | Follow key handling procedures; report missing tools or suspicious activity; lock bay doors when unattended |
| **All Employees** | Complete security onboarding; follow all policies; report incidents; protect customer data; secure workstations |

---

## 13. Policy Review and Updates

- This Security Program must be reviewed **at minimum annually**, or following:
  - A significant security incident
  - Changes to business operations, systems, or facilities
  - Changes in applicable law or regulation
- The owner is responsible for approving updates.
- All employees must be notified of material changes and sign updated acknowledgment forms.

